President Trump delivered a speech at the Normandy American Cemetery in France to commemorate the 75th anniversary of D-Day. He praised the veterans and expressed gratitude for their sacrifice. Trump highlighted the bravery and heroism displayed by the soldiers who fought on D-Day and emphasized the importance of their actions in securing freedom and democracy. He also mentioned specific individuals, such as Army medic Ray Lambert and Private First Class Russell Pickett, who demonstrated exceptional courage during the battle. Trump acknowledged the strong bond between the United States and France and thanked the French people for honoring the American soldiers buried in the cemetery. He concluded his speech by pledging unity and strength between the two nations and expressing gratitude for the veterans and the heroes of D-Day.